Great movie, it closed out the Jedi saga. With everyone coming back and Ray goes home and finds her family. Know they can make the storm trooper movie, and anything else.

I felt like the movie was rushed and included too much of a story line. The movie was my favorite of the last three and  the cinematography was beautifully executed on a positive note. I definitely want to see it againti see what I missed which is more than I can say for the rise of skywalker.
it wasn't the best stars wars movie or the worst. I enjoyed it and mostly liked how everything was wrapped up.
Despite the emotional lack lustre 3/4 of act 3, this film stands strong upon the sequel trilogy.
Very exciting and suspenseful. Great ending. Really enjoyed watching

Absolutely love this movie. I dont care what all the cry babies who think this movie should be what they want it to be. It's fun and action packed. Is the movie perfect, no, but honestly there isnt one out there.

Thoroughly enjoyable, I don't really understand the professional critics.  The movie had good pacing & action which will keep small children engaged.  The acting from the main 4 characters was fantastic.  JJ did a great job with a near impossible task.  It is definitely not perfect but who cares?  Take it for what is and enjoy the ride.

I am so pleasantly surprised after reading and watching so much hate. The movie is an amazing feat considering how difficult is to conclude such a complicated story with so many character arcs. The visuals are striking and score is great too. Adam Driver is such a great actor and Daisy Ridley is not slouch either. Love the movie. Go see it and don't listen to the negative reviews. Nowadays people forget that Star Wars was always a movie to analyse less and enjoy more, just have fun, life is short, especially if you are not the Emperor :)
